ldwide gross are as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/year/world/2020/?ref_=bo_cso_table_1|title=2020 Worldwide Box Office |website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- Note: We only link the distributor ONCE -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\"\n|+Highest-grossing films of 2020\n|-\n! Rank!! Title !! Distributor !! Worldwide gross <!--ONLY FILMS RELEASED FIRST IN 2020 WILL BE ADDED ON THIS LIST-->\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| ''[[Bad Boys for Life]]''\n| [[Sony Pictures|Sony]]\n| $425,514,702\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (film)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]''\n| [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]]\n| $306,766,470\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"| 3\n| ''[[Dolittle (film)|Dolittle]]''\n| [[Universal Pictures|Universal]]\n| $226,374,428\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 4\n| ''[[Birds of Prey (2020 film)|Birds of Prey]]''\n| [[Warner Bros.]]\n| $201,858,461\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 5\n|''[[The Invisible Man (2020 film)|The Invisible Man]]''\n| Universal\n| $124,877,252\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 6\n| ''[[The Gentlemen (2019 film)|The Gentlemen]]''\n| [[Miramax]]<!--STXfilms IS ONLY THE U.S. DISTRIBUTOR. MIRAMAX IS THE PREDOMINANTLY WORLDWIDE DISTRIBUTOR-->\n| $118,076,606\t\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 7\n| ''[[The Call of the Wild (2020 film)|The Call of the Wild]]''\n| [[20th Century Studios]]\n| $107,604,626\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 8\n| ''[[Onward (film)|Onward]]''\n| [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Disney]]\n| $104,128,230\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 9\n| ''[[Tanhaji]]''\n| [[AA Films]]\n| $52,000,000\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | 10\n| ''[[Tolo Tolo]]''\n| Medusa Film\n| $50,347,705\n|}\n\n===2020 box office records===\n\n====Film records====\n\n* ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (film)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' broke ''[[Detective Pikachu (film)|Pokemon: Detective Pikachu]]'''s record for the highest opening weekend for a [[List of films based on video games|film based on a video game]], with $70 million domestic gross in the United States and Canada.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://deadline.com/2020/02/sonic-the-hedgehog-birds-of-prey-will-ferrell-downhill-valentines-day-box-office-1202860119/ |title='Sonic The Hedgehog' Breaks Videogame Game Pic Opening Record With $70M & Reps 4th Best Presidents' Weekend Debut \u2013 Monday Update |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=February 17, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref> It went on to become the highest-grossing film based on a video game in the United States and Canada, surpassing ''Detective Pikachu''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2020/03/14/sonic-biggest-video-game-movie-jim-carrey-pokemon-ryan-reynolds-tomb-raider-angelina-jolie-warcraft-box-office/|title='Sonic The Hedgehog' Just Raced Past A Major Box Office Milestone|last=Mendelson|first=Scott|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n== Events ==\n\n===Award ceremonies===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\"\n!Date\n!Event\n!Host\n!Location\n|-\n|January 5\n|[[77th Golden Globe Awards]]\n|[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]\n|[[Beverly Hills, California|Beverly Hills]], [[California]], [[United States|U.S.]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/nbc-golden-globes-8-year-deal-1202464911/|title=NBC To Remain Golden Globes Home With New 8-Year Deal|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|date=September 14, 2018|work=Deadline|accessdate=December 2, 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203055428/https://deadline.com/2018/09/nbc-golden-globes-8-year-deal-1202464911/|archive-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|January 12\n|[[25th Critics' Choice Awards]]\n|[[Broadcast Film Critics Association]]\n|[[Santa Monica, California|Santa Monica, California, U.S]].\n|-\n|January 19\n|[