{"title_page": "List of world's fairs", "text_new": "{{See also|List of world expositions}}\n{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n\nThis is a '''list of international and colonial world's fairs''', as well as a '''list of national exhibitions''', a comprehensive chronological list of [[world's fair]]s (with notable permanent buildings built). For an annotated list of all world's fairs sanctioned by the [[Bureau International des Expositions]] (BIE), see [[List of world expositions]].\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==1790s==\n* 1791 \u2013 {{flagicon|Habsburg Monarchy}} [[Prague]], [[Bohemia]], [[Habsburg Monarchy]] \u2013 first industrial exhibition on the occasion of the coronation of [[Leopold II, Holy Roman Emperor|Leopold II]] as king of Bohemia, took place in [[Clementinum]], considerable sophistication of manufacturing methods.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/Slavonic/Czech_Hist8.html|title=The era of enlightenment|accessdate=11 March 2011|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120316114245/http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/Slavonic/Czech_Hist8.html|archivedate=16 March 2012}}</ref>\n* 1798 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[French First Republic|France]] \u2013 L'[[Exposition publique des produits de l'industrie fran\u00e7aise]], Paris, 1798.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charon.sfsu.edu/publications/PARISEXPOSITIONS/1798EXPO.HTML |title=Arthur Chandler, The First Industrial Exposition: L'Exposition publique des produits de l'industrie fran\u00e7aise, Paris, 1798 |accessdate=25 April 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080515235750/http://charon.sfsu.edu/publications/PARISEXPOSITIONS/1798EXPO.HTML |archivedate=May 15, 2008}}</ref> This was the first public industrial exposition in France although earlier in 1798 the Marquis d'Av\u00e8ze had held a private exposition of handicrafts and manufactured goods at the Maison d'Orsay in the Rue de Varenne and it was this that suggested the idea of a public exposition to Fran\u00e7ois de Neufch\u00e2teau, Minister of the Interior for the French Republic.<ref>[[Frederic Charles Danvers|F. C. Danvers]], 'International Exhibitions,' Quarterly Journal of Science 4:4 (October 1867) 488\u2013499.</ref>\n\n==1800s==\n* 1801 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[French First Republic|France]] \u2013 Second Exposition (1801). After the success of the exposition of 1798 a series of expositions for French manufacturing followed (1801, 1802, 1806, 1819, 1823, 1827, 1834, 1844 and 1849) until the first properly international (or universal) exposition in France in 1855.<ref name=\"sketch\">'Sketch of the French Expositions,' Hogg's Instructor New Series 6 (1851) 372\u2013373.</ref>\n* 1802 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[French First Republic|France]] \u2013 Third Exposition (1802)<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n* 1806 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[French First Empire|France]] \u2013 Fourth Exposition (1806)<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n\n==1810s==\n* 1819 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1814}} [[Paris]], [[Bourbon Restoration|France]] \u2013 Fifth Exposition (1819)<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n\n==1820s==\n* 1823 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1814}} [[Paris]], [[Bourbon Restoration|France]] \u2013 Sixth Exposition (1823)<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n* 1827 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1814}} [[Paris]], [[Bourbon Restoration|France]] \u2013 Seventh Exposition (1827)<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n* 1829 \u2013 {{flagicon|United States|1822}} [[New York City]], [[United States]] \u2013 [[American Institute Fair]]\n* 1829 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1816}} [[Turin]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Prima Triennale Pubblica Esposizione dell\u2019anno 1829. In Turin, a second 'triennale' followed in 1832 before other national agricultural, industrial, commercial, and applied arts expositions there in 1838, 1844, 1850 and 1858.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=NK7RkjB4f_AC&pg=PA266&lpg=PA266&dq=Prima+Triennale+Pubblica+Esposizione+dell%E2%80%99anno+1829.#v=onepage&q=Prima%20Triennale%20Pubblica%20Esposizione%20dell%E2%80%99anno%201829.&f=false|title=Arti, tecnologia, progetto: le esposizioni d'industria in Italia prima dell'unit\u00e0|last=Bigatti|first=Giorgio|last2=Onger|first2=Sergio|date=2007|publisher=FrancoAngeli|isbn=9788846485472|language=it}}</ref>\n\n==1830s==\n* 1832 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1816}} [[Turin]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Seconda Triennale Pubblica Esposizione dell\u2019anno 1832.<ref>Raimondo Riccini, 'Tracce di design. La produzione di oggetti fra tecnica e arti applicate,' in Giorgio Bigatti and Sergio Onger (eds), Arti technologi pogeto: Le exposizioni d'industria in Italia prima dell'Unit\u00e0 (Milan: FrancoAngeli, 2007) 257-276, 266.</ref>\n* 1834 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[July Monarchy|France]] \u2013 [[French Industrial Exposition of 1834]]<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n* 1838 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1816}} [[Turin]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Pubblica esposizione dell'anno 1838.<ref>Giudicio della Regia Camera di Agricoltura e di commercio di Torino sui prodotti dell'Industria de'R. Stati ammessi alla Pubblica esposizione dell'anno 1838 nelle sale del Real Castello del Valentino (Turin: Chirio e Mina, 1838).</ref>\n* 1839 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[July Monarchy|France]] \u2013 Ninth Exposition (1839)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.archivesnationales.culture.gouv.fr/chan/chan/fonds/edi/sm/sm_pdf/F12-Expositions%20avant%201850.pdf|title=Expositions publiques des produits de l'industrie fran\u00e7aise avant 1850|date=2005|website=archivesnationales.culture.gouv.fr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==1840s==\n* 1844 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[July Monarchy|France]] \u2013 [[French Industrial Exposition of 1844|French Industrial (Tenth) Exposition of 1844]]<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n* 1844 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1816}} [[Turin]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Quarta Esposizione d'Industria et di Belle Arti.<ref>Quarta esposizione di Industria e Belle arti al Real Valentino. da Remi amera di Agricoltura e di commercio di Torino, e notizie sulla patria industria, compilate da Carlo Ign. Giulio, relatore centrale (Turin: Stamperia Reale, 1844).</ref>\n* 1846 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1816}} [[Genoa]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Esposizione dei Prodotti e delle Manufatture nazionali{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n* 1849 \u2013 {{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[Birmingham]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] \u2013 Exhibition of Industrial Arts and Manufacturers<ref name=\"osler\">{{cite web|url=http://wilkinson-plc.com/osler-faraday/|accessdate=August 15, 2015|title=Osler & Faraday \u2013 Wilkinson-plc|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150831025257/http://wilkinson-plc.com/osler-faraday/|archive-date=August 31, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* 1849 \u2013 {{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[London]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] \u2013 First Exhibition of British Manufacturers (1849)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gale.com/binaries/content/assets/gale-us-en/primary-sources/intl-gps/intl-gps-essays/full-ghn-contextual-essays/ghn_essay_bln_king4_website.pdf|title=The Crystal Palace and Great Exhibition of 1851|last=King|first=Ed|date=2007|website=gale.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n* 1849 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[French Second Republic|France]] \u2013 Eleventh Exposition (1849)<ref name=\"sketch\" />\n\n==1850s==\n* 1850 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1848}} [[Turin]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Quinta Esposizione di Industria e di Belle Arti<ref>Giudizio della Regia Camera di Agricoltura e di commercio di Torino sulla quinta Esposizione di industria e di belle arti al Castello del Valentino nel 1850 et notizie sulla patria industria (Turin: 1851).</ref>\n* 1851 \u2013 {{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[London]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] \u2013 [[The Great Exhibition]] of the Works of Industry of All Nations \u2013 [[The Crystal Palace]] (typically listed as the \"first world's fair\")<ref name=\"FindPelp414\">{{cite encyclopedia\n | title = Appendix B:Fair Statistics\n | encyclopedia = Encyclopedia of World's Fairs and Expositions\n | page=414\n | editor-last = Pelle\n | editor-first = Findling\n | publisher = McFarland & Company, Inc\n | year = 2008\n | id =\n | isbn = 978-0-7864-3416-9}}</ref>\n* 1852 \u2013 {{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[Cork (city)|Cork]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] \u2013 [[Irish Industrial Exhibition]]<ref name=\"FindPelp422\">{{cite encyclopedia\n | title = Appendix D:Fairs Not Included\n | encyclopedia = Encyclopedia of World's Fairs and Expositions\n | page=422\n | editor-last = Pelle\n | editor-first = Findling\n | publisher = McFarland & Company, Inc\n | year = 2008\n | id =\n | isbn = 978-0-7864-3416-9}}</ref>\n* 1853 \u2013 {{flagicon|Two Sicilies|1816}} [[Naples]], [[Kingdom of the Two Sicilies|Two Sicilies]] \u2013 Solenne Pubblica Esposizione di Arti e Manifatture<ref>{{cite book|title=Relazione della solenne pubblica esposizione di arti e manifatture del 1853 tratta dai fascicoli XCVIII e XCIX degli Annali Civili del Regno delle Due Sicilie|last=Paci|first=Giacomo Maria|year=1854|publisher=Stab. Tip. del Ministero dell'Interno|accessdate=|url=}}</ref>\n* 1853\u20131854 \u2013 {{flagicon|United States|1851}} [[New York City|New York]], [[United States]] \u2013 [[Exhibition of the Industry of All Nations]]<ref name=\"FindPelp414\" />\n* 1853 \u2013 {{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[Dublin]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] \u2013 [[Great Industrial Exhibition (1853)]]<ref name=\"FindPelp414\" />\n* 1854 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Sardinia|1848}} [[Genoa]], [[Kingdom of Piedmont-Sardinia|Piedmont-Sardinia]] \u2013 Esposizione Industriale<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=SMsaAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA206&lpg=PA206&dq=esposizione+industriale+genoa+1854#v=onepage&q=esposizione%20industriale%20genoa%201854&f=false|title=Rivista di Firenze e bullettino delle arti del disegno ...|last=|first=|date=1858|publisher=|isbn=|location=|pages=208|language=it}}</ref>\n* 1854 \u2013 {{flagicon|Kingdom of Bavaria}} [[Munich]], [[Kingdom of Bavaria|Bavaria]] \u2013 Allgemeine deutsche Industrie-Ausstellung<ref name=\"oldbutsecondarybook\">{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/fournationalexhi00lowe|page=[https://archive.org/details/fournationalexhi00lowe/page/28 28]|accessdate=22 April 2012|title=Four national exhibitions in London and their organiser. With portraits and illustrations (1892)|publisher=London, T. F. Unwin|last=Lowe|first=Charles|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170604085029/https://archive.org/details/fournationalexhi00lowe|archive-date=4 June 2017|url-status=live|year=1892}}</ref>\n* 1854 \u2013 {{flagicon|Victoria}} [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] \u2013 Melbourne Exhibition (in conjunction with [[Exposition Universelle (1855)]])<ref name=\"oldbutsecondarybook\" />\n* 1855 \u2013 {{flagicon|France|1794}} [[Paris]], [[Second French Empire|France]] \u2013 [[Exposition Universelle (1855)]]<ref name=\"FindPelp414\" /><ref name=\"oldbutsecondarybook\" />\n*1856 \u2013 {{Flagicon|Belgium}} [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]] \u2013 International Exhibition<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=F8rUAAAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA57&lpg=RA1-PA57&dq=international+exhibition+of+domestic+economy+1869+amsterdam#v=onepage&q=international%20exhibition%20of%20domestic%20economy%201869%20amsterdam&f=false|title=The Monthly Chronicle of North-country Lore and Legend: V.1-5; Mar. 1887-De