toman Empire}} [[Jerusalem]], [[Ottoman Empire]] \u2013 [[Universal Scientific and Philanthropic Exposition (1898)]]{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]] \u2013 [[Auckland Industrial and Mining Exhibition]]{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[Dunedin]], [[New Zealand]] \u2013 [[Otago Jubilee Industrial Exhibition (1898)]]{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|United States|1896}} [[Omaha, Nebraska|Omaha]], [[United States]] \u2013 [[Trans-Mississippi Exposition]]<ref name=\"FindPelp415\" />\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|Norway|1844}} [[Bergen]], [[Sweden-Norway|Norway]] \u2013 International Fisheries Exposition (1898){{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|Germany|empire}} [[Munich]], [[German Empire|Germany]] \u2013 Kraft \u2013 und Arbeitsmaschinen-Ausstellung (1898)\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|United States|1896}} [[San Francisco]], [[United States]] \u2013 California's Golden Jubilee (1898)<ref>Not generally considered an official World's Fair as the celebration had no national pavilions or international representation. CGJ was essentially a California Exposition and not an international exposition or World's Fair.</ref>\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|Italy|1861}} [[Turin]], [[Kingdom of Italy|Italy]] \u2013 Esposizione Generale Italiana<ref name=\"p426\" />\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon|Austria-Hungary}} [[Vienna]], [[Austria-Hungary]] \u2013 Jubil\u00e4ums-Ausstellung<ref name=\"p426\" />\n* 1898 \u2013 {{flagicon |Cape Colony}} [[Grahamstown]], [[South Africa]] \u2013 [[Industrial and Arts Exhibition]]{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n* 1899 \u2013 {{flagicon|Western Australia}} [[Coolgardie]], [[Western Australia]] \u2013 Western Australian International Mining and Industrial Exhibition<ref name=\"p426\" />\n* 1899 \u2013 {{flagicon|Italy|1861}} [[Como]], [[Italy]] \u2013 [[Como Electrical Exhibition]]{{citation needed