{"title_page": "2012 UEFS Futsal Men's Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox International Football Competition\n| tourney_name = UEFS Futsal European Men's Championship\n| year = 2012\n| other_titles = X. European Men's Championship\n| image =\n| size =\n| caption = \n| country = [[Belarus]]\n| dates = 14 \u2013 19 May\n| confederations = 1\n| num_teams = 9\n| venues = 1\n| cities = 1\n| champion_other = {{futsal|BEL}}\n| count = 1\n| second_other = {{futsal|CZE}}\n| third_other = {{futsal|RUS}}\n| fourth_other = {{flagicon|CAT}} [[Catalonia men's national futsal team|Catalonia]]\n| matches = 21\n| goals = 133\n| attendance = \n| top_scorer = \n| player = \n| prevseason = [[2010 UEFS Futsal Men's Championship|2010]]\n| nextseason = [[2014 UEFS Futsal Men's Championship|2014]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2012 UEFS Futsal Men's Championship''' was the 10th men's [[European Union of Futsal|UEFS]] [[futsal]] championship, held in [[Brest, Belarus|Brest]] ([[Belarus]]) from May 14 to 19, with 9 national teams. Belgium won their first ever European championship defeating the Czech Republic 4-1 in the final.\n\n[[European Union of Futsal]] (UEFS) organizes the [[UEFS Futsal Championship|European Championship]] biennially.\n\n==Teams==\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"33%\"|\n\n{| align=center cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background: #D0E7FF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\" width=140\n|- align=center bgcolor=#006699 style=\"color:white;\"\n!width=100% colspan=2|Group A\n|-  \n|\n|{{flagicon|CAT}} [[Catalonia men's national futsal team|Catalonia]]\n|-  \n|\n|{{flagicon|RUS}} Russia\n|- \n|\n|{{flagicon|South Ossetia}} South Ossetia\n|}\n\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"33%\"|\n\n{| align=center cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background: #D0E7FF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\" width=140\n|- align=center bgcolor=#006699 style=\"color:white;\"\n!width=100% colspan=2|Group B\n|- \n|\n